text: Willem king gret mine bissupes and mine eorles and mine sirreven and alle mine þeines in þere syrren þere Wlweld abbod hauet land inne and men freondliche.

Ich kuþe geo þæt ic wille þat he beo his landuurþe sua ful and sua forþ sua he on Eaduuardes daghe kinges formest haedde, and ealre þare þe ich him suþene geunnen habbe, and his saca and his socne, tolles and taemes, and infangeneþef ofer his land and ofer his man binne burge and buten, be londen and be stronden, sua he aer best haued on allen þingen.
And ich nelle geþauien þat enig man him fram honde drage æni þare þinge þesþeich him geunnen habbe.
